#Generating a choropleth map using the plotly express module animated based on Year
import plotly.express as px

ren_energy = ren_energy.query('Year<2017 and Year>2007')

fig = px.choropleth(ren_energy, locations="Code", color="Renewable electricity (% electricity production)",
hover_name="Country", animation_frame="Year", color_continuous_scale='Greens')
In [39]:
# drawing
fig.update_layout(title_text='Renewable energy production across the world (% of electricity production)',
                 geo=dict(projection={'type': 'natural earth'}, projection_type='orthographic'))

fig.show()

import plotly.express as px
ren_energy_total_cons = ren_energy_cons[ren_energy_cons['Energy Source']=='Total'].query('Year<2017 and Year>2007')
fig2 = px.choropleth(ren_energy_cons, locations="Code", color="Consumption (terrawatt-hours)", hover_name="Country",animation_frame="Year",color_continuous_scale='Blues')
In [73]:
fig2.update_layout(
    # Add a title text for the plot
    title_text='Renewable energy consumption across the world (terrawatt-hours)',

    # Set projection style for the plot
    geo=dict(projection={'type': 'natural earth'})  # By default, projection type is set to 'equirectangular'
)

fig2.show()
